RWE CLEAN ENERGY SOLUTIONS, INC.
MARKET BASED RATES TARIFF
FEDERAL ENERGY REGULATORY COMMISSION
FERC ELECTRIC TARIFF, VOLUME NO. 1
Version 4.0.0
RWE Clean Energy Solutions, Inc. FERC Electric Tariff No. 1 Market-Based Rates Tariff
1. Availability: RWE Clean Energy Solutions, Inc. ("RWE Clean Solutions" or "Seller") may sell electric energy and capacity under this Tariff to any purchaser for resale. RWE Clean Solutions may also sell ancillary services under this Tariff into the ISO New England ("ISO-NE"), PJM Interconnection, LLC ("PJM"), New York Independent System Operator ("NYISO"), and other markets, and on a bilateral basis within those market areas. The ancillary services that RWE Clean Solutions makes available under this Tariff include:
a) New York: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, energy imbalance service, and operating reserve service (which includes 10-minute non-synchronous, 30-minute operating reserves, 10-minute spinning reserves, and 10-minute non-spinning reserves) for sale to purchasers in the market administered by the NYISO.
b) New England: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service (automatic generator control), operating reserve service (which includes 10-minute spinning reserve, 10-minute non-spinning reserve, and 30-minute operating reserve service) to purchasers within the markets administered by the ISO-NE.
c) PJM: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, energy imbalance service, and operating reserve service (which includes spinning, 10-minute, and 30-minute reserves) for sale into the market administered by PJM and, where the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff permits, the self supply of these services to purchasers for a bilateral sale that is used to satisfy the ancillary services requirements of the PJM Office of Interconnection.
d) California: Seller offers regulation service, spinning reserve service, and non-spinning reserve service to the California Independent System Operator (CAISO) and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to the CAISO.
e) MISO: Seller offers regulation service and operating reserve service (which includes 10-minute spinning reserve and 10-minute supplemental reserve) for sale to the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. (MISO) and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to MISO.
f) Southwest Power Pool: Seller offers regulation service and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute spinning reserve and 10-minute supplemental reserve) for sale to the Southwest Power Pool, Inc. (SPP) and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to SPP.
g) Third-Party Ancillary Services: Seller offers Regulation Service, Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service, Energy and Generator Imbalance Service, Operating Reserve-Spinning, Operating Reserve Supplemental, and Primary Frequency Response Service. Sales will not include the following: (1) sales to an RTO or an ISO, i.e., where that entity has no ability to self-supply ancillary services but instead depends on third parties; and (2) sales to a traditional, franchised public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier, or sales where the underlying transmission service is on the system of the public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier. Sales of Operating Reserve-Spinning and Operating Reserve-Supplemental will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except where the Commission has granted authorization. Sales of Regulation Service and Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except at rates not to exceed the buying public utility transmission provider's OATT rate for the same service or where the Commission has granted authorization.
2. Applicability: This Schedule is applicable to all sales of energy, capacity, or ancillary services by Seller not otherwise subject to a particular rate schedule of Seller or the NYISO, ISO-NE, or PJM.
3. Rates: All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and Seller.
4. Seller Category: Seller is a Category 2 seller, as defined in 18 C.F.R. 35.36(a), in the following regions: Northeast and Southwest. Seller is a Category 1 seller, as defined in 18 C.F.R. 35.36(a), in the following regions: Central, Southeast, Northwest, and Southwest Power Pool, as defined in 18 CFR 35.36(a).
5. Other Terms and Conditions: All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and Seller.
6. Compliance with Commission Regulations: Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Seller's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Seller to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits Seller's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning Seller's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff
7. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority: The following limitations and exemptions or waivers to the Commission's regulations apply to sales under this tariff:
a) RWE Clean Solutions is exempt from Parts 41, 101 (with the exception that waiver of the provisions of Part 101 that apply to hydropower licensees is not granted with respect to licensed hydropower projects), and 141 of the Commission's regulations concerning accounting and reporting requirements, with the exception of 18 C.F.R. 141.14 and 141.15. Consolidated Edison of New York et al., 78 FERC 61,298 (1997).
b) RWE Clean Solutions has blanket authorization for the issuances of securities or assumptions of liabilities pursuant to section 204 of the FPA, 16 U.S.C. 824(d). Consolidated Edison of New York et al., 78 FERC 61,298 (1997).
c) RWE Clean Solutions is exempt from the provisions of Subparts B and C of Part 35 of the Commission's regulations, with the exception of sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15, and 35.16. Consolidated Edison of New York et al., 78 FERC 61,298 (1997). Consolidated Edison Solutions, Inc. Page 1 Market Based Rates Tariff, FERC Electric Tariff, Volume No. 1
